thumb|Deadwood circa 1890s
Dodge City is a city in and the county seat of Ford County, Kansas, USA. It was named after Colonel Richard Irving Dodge.
Image:Deadwood13.jpg|thumb|A photograph of Deadwood in 1876.
 The population was 25,176 at the 2000 census.
 General view of the Dakota Territory gold rush town from a hillside above.
thumb|The Gem in 1878
  The city's name is well known to generations of Americans, as the long-running old-time radio and television Western drama program Gunsmoke was set in Dodge City.
Image:Cyark Deadwood Bullock Clark.jpg|thumb|Photo-textured 3D laser scan image of Bullock-Clark Building, 616-618 Main Street (1894)
Image:Cyark Deadwood Hickock.jpg|thumb|Possible current location of the original Nuttal & Mann's saloon where Wild Bill Hickok was killed, 624 Main Street, Deadwood
thumb|left|Buffalo Hunter Ralph Morrison who was killed and scalped December 7, 1868 near Fort Dodge Kansas by Cheyennes.
Deadwood, named for the dead trees found in its gulch, is a city in and the county seat of Lawrence County, South Dakota, United States.
