 Cooney was transferred to Fort Bayard, near Silver City, New Mexico in 1870.
In May 1885, Baca was charged with murder for the death of the one of the Jon Slaughter's foreman and Bert Hearne.
The town attained notoriety for the murder of Wild Bill Hickok, and remains the final resting place of Hickok and Calamity Jane, as well as slightly less notable figures such as Seth Bullock.
 While scouting for the 8th U.S. Cavalry north of Mogollon and east of Alma, he discovered silver ore in the Mogollon Mountains.
 It became known for its wild and almost lawless reputation, during which time murder was common, and punishment for murders not always fair and impartial.
