The western movement of settlers brought conflict with the Indians.
 Killing far exceeded market requirements, reaching over one million per year.
 Scores of Indian wars and campaigns were fought by the Army.
 The Fashion arrived back at Indianola and unloaded the camels on May 14, 1856.
